      • checkComponentDependencies

        public void checkComponentDependencies(boolean isExternalAllowed)
        Recursively check all component dependencies referenced directly or indirectly by the wrapped component. Verify that all dependencies exist and that the dependency graph is free of cycles. Dependencies on resources not defined as MaskingComponents in this API are not checked.
        Parameters:
        isExternalAllowed - Whether dependencies may exist outside of the plugin that provided the component
        Throws:
        InvalidDependencyException - When a dependency is invalid or would result in a dependency loop
        MissingDependencyException - When a dependency is missing

      • getAlgorithmByName

        public <U> MaskingAlgorithm<U> getAlgorithmByName(@Nonnull
                                                  AlgorithmInstanceReference algorithmReference,
                                                  @Nonnull
                                                  MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType type,
                                                  @Nonnull
                                                  MaskValueMetadata metadata)
        Description copied from interface: ComponentService
        Get a MaskingAlgorithm object for the algorithm specified by the reference and type. It is only possible to find named instances of component algorithms using this method. The returned MaskingAlgorithm object is fully initialized and ready to mask data. The algorithm object created will be set to the same MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingMode value as the caller.
        Specified by:
        getAlgorithmByName in interface ComponentService
        Type Parameters:
        U - The data type masked by the returned algorithm, must exactly match what is requested in type
        Parameters:
        algorithmReference - A reference describing the algorithm instance to get
        type - The masking data type the named algorithm is expected mask
        metadata - The mask value metadata for the values that will be passed to the instance being created
        Returns:
        A masking algorithm object

      • getMaskValueMetadata

        public MaskValueMetadata getMaskValueMetadata()
        Description copied from interface: ComponentService
        Retrieve the metadata access interface for the masked field. This metadata includes values such as date format, maximum string length, etc. This method may only be invoked by single-column algorithm instances; that is, algorithms that do not consume GenericData objects. In cases where metadata is not available, this method will return null.
        Specified by:
        getMaskValueMetadata in interface ComponentService
        Returns:
        A metadata object describing the values to be masked, or null if metadata is not available.
